manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Keep Your Children & Family Safe Keep your family safe with our most comprehensive all-purpose First Aid Kit. From minor cuts & scrapes to all the mishaps children may get into, we've got you covered. Feel safe knowing that no consumable pharmaceuticals are included in this kit that could pose a danger to small children. Does this First Aid Kit meet Workplace Requirements? Our kit meets requirements for most small businesses and work sites. To increase safety to small children, no consumable pharmaceuticals accompany this kit, so for larger corporations or work sites where risk of injury to employees is deemed greater, you may supplement this kit with appropriate items such as aspirin, antibiotic ointment, and burn gel to ensure adherence to state and local regulations. Organization & Extra Space Smart organization and item layout into 20 individual quick-access compartments means you can quickly find and get to all 348 items in case of emergencies. Includes extra space to customize with your own first aid supplies.

Extra Mini Kit Included Small, portable, & light, perfect companion for taking with you traveling or just out and about in town. Easily fits into purses, handbags, backpack pockets, and car gloveboxes. Double-Sided Heavy Duty Case Rugged water-resistant case measures 10x12x3" and is built to the highest quality standards for durability and longevity to withstand the rigors of both the home and the workplace. Secure Latching Mechanism Dual latches on each side of the case lock securely into place ensuring contents remain inside at all times. Double-sided case layout maximizes surface area to volume ratio to keep items easily accessible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars decent variety for the price, missing meds
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this kit for a vehicle, and it is very compact (about the size of a large adult hand). The variety of items in this pack was great, but I would probably give it three stars as a family first aid kit. The pack does include something for stings, but other than that, there are not any medication supplies (as seen in the list of items on the kit's description). I'm not sure why a mirror & fishing kit were more important than antibiotic ointment and painkillers. I had to purchase medications separately, and I found most of the medications I wanted with the Pak-Kit and with PreparaKit's First Aid Kit Refill Bag . This Swiss Safe kit was packed fairly tight, but I was able to add a few things.Items NOT included (some more important than others) are: painkillers (Aspirin, Ibuprofen, Acetaminophen), nasal decongestant, antihistamine & allergy meds, antacid, motion sickness meds, antibiotic ointments, burn cream, hydrocortisone cream, lip balm, or sunscreen.I was also hoping for a waterproof pack, but this at best would be water resistant. If I spill water on it, I think it would hold up to that, but if I dropped the kit in water, I do not have high hopes for its water resistance. Most of the items ARE individually bagged, so if water gets in, they may stand a chance of being salvageable.Overall, this was a decent deal for the price but needs some improvement.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 26, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Decent 1st aid kit
reviews.reviewText: We needed an emergency 1st aid kit for road trips and so on. We wanted an all in one, includes everything in it kit that we could toss in the backseat or throw in a backpack. It had to be sturdy enough not to crush and easily found.Well, this fit all the requirements. It opens either way so it hold more variety and that's both good and bad. It has a bit of everything but not a lot of anything. It's perfect for a road trip, but make sure you have stuff to refill when you get home.All in all, I feel safer with it than without. That alone makes it worth it. But when you need it, you really realize how worth it, it truly is.I would recommend, seriously get this. It's a great value, it's perfect for around the house or shop... and great for traveling. Nice and sturdy.
